Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said he was discharged from the hospital on Wednesday morning two days after he was admitted with an intestinal blockage. Sharing photos with doctors on Twitter, Bolsonaro confirmed his discharge and thanked those who took care of him. The president, who had been on vacation in the southern state of Santa Catarina, was rushed to the Vila Nova Star Hospital in Sao Paulo with intestinal blockage on Monday. The doctors said he would not require surgery. Covid-19: England To Suspend PCR Confirmation Of Positive Testâ€¦ Russian-US Security Talks To Be Held On Jan. 10 In Geneva Bolsonaro has undergone four surgeries due to the stabbing he suffered during a 2018 election campaign event.